Boba Fett \

Keywords:bomber, rogue
Card Text

When you activate, choose 1 enemy ship or squadron at distance 1. That ship or squadron suffers 1 damage.

Timing
This Squadron Card effect resolves when the squadron is activated.

Clarifications

  • If an enemy ship is chosen to suffer 1 damage, the controlling player of that ship chooses which hull zone that damage is suffered to. [1]
  • You may not target a friendly squadron with this Squadron Card effect. [1]
  • If this Squadron is unactivated, and its activation slider is toggled to the activated side by a card or ability effect, this Squadron Card effect is not triggered. [1]
  • A fleet (or allied fleets) cannot have both Boba Fett (Squadron) and This squadron. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • Biggs Darklighter or Axe cannot reduce damage dealt from this Squadron Card effect. [1]

Colonel Jendon \

Keywords:heavy, relay 2
Card Text

During your activation, instead of attacking, you may choose 1 friendly squadron at distance 1-2. That squadron may perform an attack (even if it has already activated).

Timing
This Squadron Card effect may be resolved during this Squadron’s activation.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron Card effect can resolve even if this Squadron is not engaged or is unable to perform an attack due to some other effect. [1]
  • This Squadron Card effect does not activate the chosen squadron. [1]
  • If this Squadron is activated by a squadron command, it can resolve its card ability before or after moving. [1]
  • If this Squadron was not activated by a squadron command, during the Squadron Phase, this Squadron can only move OR attack. This means this Squadron cannot move and then utilize its ability or vice versa [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • If a ship equipped with Flight Controllers activates this Squadron, and this Squadron uses his ability to cause another friendly squadron to perform an attack, that squadron’s armament is not increased by Flight Controllers’s effect. [1]

Darth Vader \

Keywords:escort
Card Text

While attacking, each of your T icons adds 1 damage to the damage total.

Timing
This Upgrade Card may be resolved when a ship is attacking during the "Resolve Attack Effects” step.

Clarifications

  • While a friendly ship is attacking, during the "Resolve Attack Effects" step, it can spend a defense token to reroll any die in its attack pool, even if the attacking ship is at speed 0. Speed 0 only prevents a ship from spending tokens during the “Spend Defense Tokens” step of an attack. [1]
  • You cannot use this ability when attacking squadrons or proximity mines. [1]
  • Intel Officer allows you to target your own defense tokens. If that defense token is chosen by this Upgrade Card to be spent for a reroll, that defense token would be discarded. Damage Card Interactions [1]
  • If a ship has the critical card Faulty Countermeasures (“You cannot spend exhausted defense tokens.”) you may not spend an exhausted defense token for this card’s ability. [1]

Hondo Ohnaka

Keywords:bomber, grit, rogue
Card Text

During your activation, instead of attacking, you may toggle the activation slider of 1 squadron at distance 1 to the activated side. If it was already activated, you may place it anywhere at distance 1 of you.

Timing
This Upgrade Card may resolve at the start of the Ship Phase.

Clarifications

  • At the start of the ship phase, a ship equipped with this Upgrade Card may choose to discard this card. If you do, you choose 2 different command tokens and place them on 2 different ships. Then your opponent chooses 2 different command tokens that you did not choose and also places them on 2 different ships. [1]
  • The tokens must be assigned to a ship, even if you must assign it to an enemy ship (for example you only have 1 ship in the play area). [1]
  • Your opponent can assign a token to a ship that was already given a token by you. [1]
  • When assigning a token to a ship, if a ship already holds its maximum number of command tokens according to its command value, the player that controls that ship may decide to either replace a current command token with that assigned token, or to discard the command token that was assigned. [1]
  • You can assign a token from this Upgrade Card to a ship that already has the same token already. It is then immediately discarded, unless that ship can hold multiple command tokens of the same type. [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • If this Upgrade Card is used and Tantive IV is selected to receive a token, it may pass the token to be gained. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Howlrunner \

Keywords:swarm
Card Text

While another friendly squadron with Swarm at distance 1 is attacking a squadron, it may add 1 blue die to its attack pool.

Timing
This Squadron Card effect may resolve during the "Resolve Attack Effects" step.

Squadron Interactions

  • The extra blue die from this Squadron Card is added after the initial attack pool is rolled. This means if no attack pool can be formed (such as a squadron with one die in its anti-squadron armament attacking an obstructed target), the blue die will not be added to the attack pool as the attack will be cancelled. [1]

Major Rhymer \

Keywords:bomber, heavy
Card Text

Friendly squadrons at distance 1 can attack enemy ships at close range using all dice in their battery armament.

Timing
This Squadron Card is resolved during the "Declare Target" step.
This Squadron Card effect resolves after each time the squadron moves.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron Card effect includes Major Rhymer himself. [1]
  • When a friendly squadron attacks using this Squadron Card effect, it ignores the dice color restrictions on the range side of the ruler, rolling all dice in its battery armament. [1]
  • Swarm [1]
  • This Squadron Card effect will not damage friendly squadrons, as a squadron does not engage friendly squadrons. [1]
  • When a squadron moves, it can choose to remain in its current position and is still considered to have moved. A squadron can only choose to do so if it is eligible to move (through effects such as Grit or Admiral Chiraneau). In this case, this Squadron Card effect would damage the enemy squadrons it is engaged with. [1]
  • Squadrons are sometimes “placed” rather than “moved”, such as by Hondo Ohnaka (Slave 1\) or after being overlapped by a ship. “Placement” does not trigger this Squadron Card effect. [1]
  • Squadrons that are obstructed from this Squadron are not engaged, and thus would not take damage from this Squadron Card effect. [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • This Squadron can trigger its ability from a Fighter Coordination Team move. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • Biggs Darklighter or Axe cannot reduce damage dealt from this Squadron Card effect. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Valen Rudor \

Keywords:swarm
Card Text

While an enemy squadron is engaged with another squadron, it cannot attack you.

Timing
This Squadron Card is resolved during an attacker's "Declare Target" step.

Clarifications

  • An enemy squadron engaged with another squadron cannot perform a Counter attack against this Squadron. [1]
  • If an enemy squadron is engaged with this Squadron and also engaged with another friendly squadron (even if that squadron lacks Escort) the enemy squadron cannot attack Valen Rudor. [1]
  • If an enemy squadron with Snipe is engaged by another friendly squadron at distance 1, and this Squadron is within the distance 2 range band, the enemy squadron cannot Snipe Valen Rudor. [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • If an enemy squadron is at distance 1 of Instigator and engaged with Valen Rudor, Instigator’s "ghost" squadrons prevent the enemy squadron from attacking Valen Rudor. However, in that case, if a squadron has no other valid targets, they can attack a ship (in this case, Instigator). [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • Anakin Skywalker (Y-wing)’s card effect, when resolved, can allow an attack on this Squadron [1]
  • This Squadron cannot be attacked by IG-88 if IG-88 is also engaged with other enemy squadrons (even those with Escort). [1]
  • This Squadron cannot be attacked during IG-88B‘s ability if IG-88B is also engaged with other enemy squadrons. [1]

Biggs Darklighter [

Keywords:bomber, escort
Card Text

Before a friendly squadron with Escort at distance 1 suffers damage during an attack, you may reduce the total damage by 1. If you do, choose a frienly squadron with Escort at distance 1. That squadron suffers 1 damage.

Timing
This Squadron Card resolves during the “Resolve Damage” step.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron Effect may target itself. [1]
  • If "Dutch" Vander is attacking and this Squadron’s effect prevents the defender from suffering damage, "Dutch" Vander’s effect does not toggle the defender’s activation slider (or that of the other squadron). [1]
  • If Anakin Skywalker (Delta-7) is attacking and this Squadron’s effect prevents the defender from suffering damage, Anakin Skywalker (Delta-7)’s ability would not resolve. [1]
  • This Squadron’s ability may be resolved for each damage that would be applied by damage dealt during an attack such as; Orbital Bombardment Particle Cannon, Ten Numb, Anakin Skywalker (Delta-7), and Wide-Area Barrage, as long as all of this Squadron’s conditions are met. [1]
  • Ruthless Strategists damage cannot be moved by this Squadron’s ability, as the damage takes place after (not during) an attack. [1]
  • This Squadron cannot move damage to a friendly squadron that has been destroyed yet is still in play due to General Rieekan's ability. [1]

  • While this Squadron is attacking, you may reroll 1 die for each enemy squadron or ship that is at distance 1. This applies to both ships and squadrons simultaneously. Example: 1 enemy ship, reroll 1 die. 2 enemy squadrons, reroll 2 dice. 2 enemy squadrons and 1 enemy ship, reroll 3 dice. [1]
  • Bomber [1]
  • Heavy [1]
  • A squadron is considered either activated or unactivated based on its activation slider. A squadron that was activated and then has its activation slider toggled with Adar Tallon’s ability is no longer considered activated for this Squadron Card’s ability. [1]
  • If this Squadron is attacking and the defender does not suffer damage but another enemy squadron does (due to resolving an effect such as Biggs Darklighter or “Axe”), this Squadron’s effect does not toggle either the defender’s activation slider nor any other squadron damaged in the attack. [1]

Fenn Rau [

Keywords:assault, escort
Card Text

When you are chosen to activate by a Squadron command, after the activation is resolved, choose up to 2 non-unique squadrons at Distance 1. The chosen squads may activate as if they were chosen by the Squadron command.

Timing
This Upgrade Card resolves when resolving a Squadron command, after activating this squadron .

Upgrade Interactions

  • Upgrade card effects that affect squadrons activated by a ship (such as Yavaris or Flight Controllers) also affect squadrons chosen by this squadron’s ability when they activate. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • The squadrons chosen by this Squadron Card’s effect must be unactivated in order to be chosen. [1]
  • Squadrons chosen to be activated by this Squadron Card’s ability do not count as part of the total squadron activation of the ship that activated this squadron. They are additional squadron activations. [1]
  • This Squadron Card’s ability to choose two squadrons to activate may be resolved when this squadron card is activated by a Squadron token. [1]

Lando Calrissian [

Keywords:grit, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, you may discard a defense token to set 1 die to any face. That die cannot be modified again.

While defending you may spend 1 of your defense tokens to force the attacker to reroll 1 or more dice of your choice.

Timing
This Upgrade Card may be discarded during the "Spend Defense Tokens" step.
This Squadron Card may resolve during the "Resolve Attack Effects" step when attacking and during the "Spend Defense Tokens" step when defending.

Clarifications

  • Any accuracies rolled as a result of this Upgrade Card cannot be spent as the timing window (Resolve Attack Effects) has passed. However, a ship with SW-7 Ion Batteries equipped can use any blue die accuracies as damage, as they are “unspent”. [1]
  • Setting a die to an Accuracy icon with this Squadron’s ability is useless as that die cannot be spent to target a defense token. This is because a die changed by this Squadron cannot be modified again, and spending an Accuracy is modifying the die. [1]
  • While this Squadron is defending, you cannot spend a Brace defense token to resolve the card ability and also spend another Brace defense token to resolve Brace; you cannot spend more than one defense token of each type per attack. [1]
  • While this Squadron is defending, any defense tokens targeted by Accuracies cannot be spent to resolve this Squadron Card's ability. [1]
  • A fleet (or allied fleets) cannot have both this Squadron and Han Solo (Squadron). [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • Targeting Scrambler nor Evade, (or other cards/effects such as these, including this Squadron) cannot “reroll” a die that has been modified by this Squadron card effect. [1]
  • Captain Brunson and Scatter (or other cards/effects such as these) cannot “cancel” a die that has been modified by this Squadron card effect. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • This Squadron, while defending, cannot spend defense tokens from Jan Ors to resolve the card ability as it is not one of “your” (as in, that squadron’s) defense tokens. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Kickback |

Keywords:escort, swarm
Card Text

After you perform an attack, you may move up to distance 1, even if you are engaged.

Timing
Counter & Salvo interactions: If both players have effects with the same timing, the first player resolves all of their effects with that timing first.​​​​​​​ If two or more of a player’s effects have the same timing, that player can resolve those effects in any order. If this Squadron Card belongs to the first player, this Squadron Card must resolve its effect and move before the Counter attack is performed by the second player. If this Squadron Card belongs to the second player, the first player Counter would happen first, followed by this Squadron’s movement. If this Squadron moves out of distance 1 of a squadron that will be performing Counter, the Counter will still resolve. Counter is NOT limited by attack range; it states that if you are attacked by a non Counter attack, you may attack that squadron. Counter is, however, impacted by obstruction. This Squadron may move in such a way that the subsequent Counter shot is obstructed. Salvo uses the range and line of sight of the original attack and thus would not be affected by this Squadron moving into a different range band or into obstruction.

Card Text

During your activation, instead of attacking, you may discard a command token from an enemy ship at distance 1-2. If you do, a friendly ship at distance 1-3 may gain a matching command token.

This Squadron's ability can be resolved at any point during its activation and may be resolved even if it is engaged.

Count Dooku }

Keywords:adept 2, cloak, rogue
Card Text

While a friendly squadron without Ai at range 1-2 is attacking a squadron, it may suffer 1 damage. If it does, it may reroll 1 die. If that squadron has screen, it may instead reroll up to 2 dice.

Timing
This Squadron's first ability applies during all points in a turn when it is unactivated.
A squadron is considered activated once you announce that you are activating them. Their slider is then toggled at the end of the activation to track that they have been activated. This means that during this Squadron's activation, it would lose Dodge 1 and gain an additional Adept 1 from the ability.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron's ability applies to itself, as it is at distance 1 of itself and the ability doesn't specify “other” friendly squadrons. [1]
  • As with the rule on keywords, if a squadron gains a stackable keyword such as Adept or Dodge from multiple sources, unless specified otherwise through text like “to a maximum of”, this squadron's ability will stack. [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • If this Squadron is the target of Flechette Torpedoes and its activation slider is toggled to the activated side, then this Squadron's ability would switch from granting Dodge 1 to Adept 1. [1]
  • If this Squadron is selected by 7I-99 to perform a Counter attack, as the activation slider is toggled after the Counter attack is completed, this Squadron's effect would still grant Dodge 1, and not Adept 1 until after the activation slider is toggled to the activated side. [1]
  • If this Squadron is activated before the start of the Squadron Phase, all friendly squadrons without Ai at distance 1 will have Adept, and therefore may resolve the first effect of Hot Landing to gain Grit. If a friendly squadron without Ai were to lose this Squadron's effect, as an example by moving out of range or this Squadron being destroyed, then it does not have Adept to resolve Hot Landing's second effect. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • If Hondo Ohnaka (Slave I) activates this Squadron using its ability, then this Squadron switches from granting Dodge 1 to Adept 1. [1]
  • When this Squadron defends against an attack from Dutch Vander, if it is unactivated before the attack, it has Dodge 1 and may resolve the Dodge keyword on dice from Dutch Vander's attack. If this Squadron were to suffer damage to resolve Dutch's ability, and it may perform a Counter attack, then it would have Adept for that Counter attack as Dutch's ability resolves during the Resolve Damage step, and Counter attacks happen after the Resolve Damage step. [1]

Obstacle Interactions

  • If an Exogorth deals damage to this Squadron and toggles its activation slider to the activated side, then this Squadron switches from granting Dodge 1 to Adept 1. [1]
[1] Legacy | 2025-07-17 | FAQ 1.1

Darth Maul }

Keywords:cloak, dodge 1, rogue
Card Text

If you are engaged with at least 2 enemy squadrons, gain Adept 1. For each additional squadron you are engaged with, increase your Adept value by 1.

Timing
This Squadron's ability applies whenever it is engaged with 2 or more enemy squadrons.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron's ability applies to all attacks initiated by this squadron. For example, if this Squadron is engaged with 2 or more Heavy squadrons and performs an anti-ship attack, the engagement condition is met to activate this Squadron's ability, and therefore it has the Adept and may resolve it for that attack. [1]
  • Additional effects that key off of the Adept keyword apply to this Squadron when it meets the condition of its ability. [1]
  • Additional instances of the Adept keyword will stack with this Squadron's ability. For example, if Count Dooku (Squadron) gives this Squadron Adept 1, and this squadron is already engaged with 2 squadrons, it will increase its Adept by 1 to Adept 2. [1]

Upgrade Interactions

  • If this Squadron is activated through TI-99 and gains Counter, if it is engaged with at least 2 enemy squadrons it may resolve the Adept keyword for that Counter attack. [1]
  • As this squadron has Adept gained as a keyword when the engagement condition is met, both effects of the Hot Landing upgrade card apply to this squadron while the condition is active. In addition, if this squadron were to lose the engagement condition, therefore losing Adept, and it is destroyed, it will not resolve the second effect of Hot Landing as it no longer has that keyword. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • Squadrons that ignore engagement, such as Anakin Skywalker (BTL-B), do not count towards the engaged squadron total while their ability is active, as they bypass keywords or card effects that trigger on engagement. For example, this Squadron is engaged with two squadrons, a generic non-Escort squadron and Anakin Skywalker (BTL-B). If Anakin Skywalker (BTL-B) activates, spends a defense token to ignore engagement, and then performs an attack against this Squadron, if this Squadron is to perform a Counter attack against Anakin Skywalker (BTL-B), then that Counter attack will not gain the benefit of this squadron's effect, as it is “only engaged” with one squadron for the duration of the ability. [1]

Counter and Salvo Interactions

  • As this Squadron's ability specifies that the squadron gains Adept when under the engagement condition, Counter attacks made when the engagement condition is met may resolve Adept. [1]

General Grievous }

Keywords:relay 2, screen
Card Text

While attacking a ship or squadron with no readied defense tokens, each of your Crit adds 1 damage to the total.

Timing
The effect of this card triggers immediately upon the destruction of a friendly ship or squadron at distance 1-5.
This Squadron Card resolves during the “Resolve Damage” step.

Clarifications

  • If a player chooses to resolve the Reserve Hangar Deck effect when a squadron is destroyed, the squadron is still considered destroyed and would resolve this Upgrade Card’s effect. These effects share a timing window and can be resolved in the order of the controlling player's choice. [1]
  • The squadron’s position when it was destroyed would be used when determining distance for this Upgrade Card effect, not the squadron’s position after being placed by Reserve Hangar Deck. [1]
  • If a player chooses to move a ship or squadron so that any of it is outside of the play area; i.e., fly it off the board, it is considered destroyed and would trigger this Upgrade Card’s effect. [1]
  • This Upgrade Card’s effect can resolve when a friendly Unarmed Stations is destroyed as Unarmed Stations are treated as ships when resolving effects. [1]
  • This Squadron Card’s effect applies to any ship or squadron that does not have a readied defense token. This includes squadrons or ships that have never had any defense tokens, such as generic squads or non-tokened aces. [1]
  • If the defender had a single “readied” defense token, and they spent that token in the “Spend Defense tokens” step so that they no longer have any readied defense tokens, this would allow this Squadron Card’s effect to resolve in the “Resolve Damage” step. Defense Token Interactions [1]
  • If the defender spends a Brace token and then no longer has any readied defense tokens, this Squadron’s effect will take effect first, before damage is halved by the Brace effect. This may potentially increase the total damage suffered despite the Brace token being spent. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Haor Chall Prototypes }

Keywords:ai antisquadron 1, swarm
Card Text

Before an enemy ship or squadron at distance 1 moves, you may perform an attack against that ship or squadron even if you are engaged.

Timing
This Squadron Card may resolve before an enemy ship or squadron moves.

Clarifications

  • An enemy squadron, if engaged with this squadron and otherwise able to move, can choose to forego movement to prevent this squadron’s effect from triggering. [1]
  • A ship’s movement will trigger this squadron’s effect. [1]

Squadron Interactions

  • If this Squadron is engaged by a squadron with Escort, this Squadron will not be able to attack any non-Escort squadrons with its Squadron Card effect. [1]
  • If this Squadron is engaged with other enemy squadrons, it cannot use its ability to attack Valen Rudor. [1]
  • If an enemy squadron is activated by a ship and moves while engaged with this Squadron, this squadron may attack it. This attack granted by this squadron card would occur during the enemy squadron’s activation - meaning that the enemy squadron's Counter would gain any effects that last during the span of its activation (such as Flight Controllers) [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Jango Fett }

Keywords:bomber, grit, rogue
Card Text

While attacking a unique squadron during your activation, you may deal 1 damage to another friendly squadron at distance 1 of the defender. If you do, you may change 1 die to any face.

Timing
This Squadron Card’s effect resolves while attacking, but would not trigger during an attack outside of Jango's activation, such as a Counter attack.

Clarifications

  • You may change the die to an Accuracy face and spend it. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Phlac-Arphocc Prototypes }

Keywords:ai antisquadron 1, counter 2, swarm
Card Text

After an enemy squadron ends its activation at distance 1, that squadron suffers 1 damage.

Timing
This Squadron Card effect may resolve when an enemy squadron ends its activation.

Clarifications

  • This Squadron Card effect’s damage is suffered regardless of any movement, obstruction, or engagement. [1]
  • This damage granted by this ability does not occur as part of an attack, and therefore cannot be ameliorated by defense tokens or abilities which trigger as part of an attack (such as Biggs Darklighter) [1]
  • Effects that “toggle” a squadron’s activation slider to the activated side (such as Exogorths or “Dutch” Vander) do not trigger this Squadron Card’s effect as a “toggle” is not the same as that squadron having activated. [1]
[1] ARC | 2025-07-11 | ARM 1.03

Nexus Ace Squadrons 8

Lieutenant Karsabi \

Keywords:bomber, scout
Card Text

While attacking a ship, if there is at least 1 friendly unengaged squadron with Bomber within distance 1 of you, you may add a red die to your attack pool.

Rho Squadron \

Keywords:bomber, scout
Card Text

While attacking a ship, if there is at least 1 friendly unengaged squadron with Bomber within distance 1 of you, you may add a red die to your attack pool.

Seventh Sister \

Keywords:adept 1
Card Text

While defending against a unique squadron, when you would reroll a die, you may cancel it instead.

The Grand Inquisitor \

Card Text

While attacking a unique squadron, you may set 1 die to any face.

Corran Horn

Keywords:bomber, snipe 4
Card Text

Once per round, after you perform an attack, you may spend a defense token to perform an additional attack against the same target using an anti-squadron armament of 2 blue dice.

Gavin Darklighter

Keywords:bomber, snipe 4
Card Text

After an enemy squadron at distance 1-2 of you suffers damage from a squadron attack, you may spend a readied defense token. If you do, the defender suffers 1 damage.

Keyan Farlander

Keywords:assault, bomber
Card Text

While attacking a ship, if the defending hull zone has no shields, you may reroll any number of dice in your attack pool.

Luke Skywalker

Keywords:adept 2, bomber, snipe 4
Card Text

While attacking, after you roll your attack pool, if there is an U icon in your attack pool, you may add one die of any color to the attack pool.

Mara Jade

Keywords:counter 3
Card Text

Enemy squadrons at distance 1 of you cannot move.

Miranda Doni

Keywords:bomber, counter 1, scout
Card Text

While performing an attack against a squadron,m your may decrease your anti-squadron armament by 1 die to recover 1 hull point, or suffer 1 damage to increase your anti-squadron armament by 1 blue die.

Pash Cracken

Keywords:counter 3
Card Text

Enemy squadrons at distance 1 of you cannot move.

Tycho Celchu

Keywords:bomber, escort, grit
Card Text

When a friendly squadron with Escort at distance 1 is declared as the target of an attack, you may spend 1 defense token to treat the attack as obstructed.

Wedge Antilles

Keywords:bomber, escort
Card Text

While attacking an activated squadron, if the defender is engaged with another friendly squadron with Escort, you may add 2 blue dice to the attack pool.

Cassian Andor [

Keywords:assault, intel, scout
Card Text

While a friendly squadron at distance 1 is defending, you may spend 1 defense token to force the attacker to reroll 1 die of your choice.

Delta Squad |

Keywords:assault, grit, heavy, swarm
Card Text

When you assign a raid token, you may discard 1 matching command token from the defender. You are not prevented from attacking ships while engaged with 2 or fewer squadrons.

Klick |

Keywords:counter 2, swarm
Card Text

When you perform an attack with Counter against a unique squadron, increase your Counter by 1.

Quinlan Vos |

Keywords:dodge 1, rogue
Card Text

While deploying fleets, you count as deploying two squadrons.

Bo-Katan Kryze {

Keywords:assault, cloak, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, if you are touching the defender's base, you may reroll up to 2 dice.

Boba Fett {

Keywords:bomber, rogue
Card Text

When you activate, choose 1 enemy ship or squadron at distance 1. That ship or squadron suffers 1 damage.

Bossk {

Keywords:grit, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, if you have 6 or fewer hull points remaining, you may add 1 blue die set to the U icon to your attack pool.

Captain Jostero {

Keywords:escort, screen

Dash Rendar {

Keywords:bomber, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, you may reroll 1 die for each enemy squadron or enemy ship at distance 1.

Dengar {

Keywords:intel, swarm
Card Text

While another friendly squadron is at distance 1-2, it has Counter 1 or increases its Counter value by 1.

Din Djarin {

Keywords:rogue
Card Text

While attacking, if there are no other friendly squadrons at distance 1 of you, you may reroll up to 2 of your dice.

Fenn Rau {

Keywords:counter 2, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, if the defender is at distance 1-3 from a friendly ship with the Mandalorian tag, you may change 1 die to any face.

Gar Saxon {

Keywords:counter 2, rogue
Card Text

While a friendly 'Mandalorian' squadron at distance 1 is attacking a squadron with adept or dodge, it may add 1 red die to a face with an U icon to its attack pool.

Greedo {

Keywords:grit, rogue
Card Text

During the Ship Phase, when an enemy squadron at distance 1-3 would activate, you may toggle your activation slider to the activated side to immediately activate as if by a 8 command.

Guri {

Keywords:cloak, grit
Card Text

At the start of the squadron phase, you may activate as if activated by a 8 command.

Han Solo {

Keywords:grit, rogue
Card Text

At the start of the Ship Phase, you may activate as if you were activated by a 8 command.

Hondo Ohnaka

Keywords:bomber, grit, rogue
Card Text

During your activation, instead of attacking, you may toggle the activation slider of 1 squadron at distance 1 to the activated side. If it was already activated, you may place it anywhere at distance 1 of you.

Kad Solus {

Keywords:counter 2, rogue
Card Text

You ignore the dodge and escort keywords on enemy squadrons.

Kavil {

Keywords:escort, swarm
Card Text

When you overlap an obstacle, you may recover 1 hull.

Lando Calrissian {

Keywords:grit, rogue
Card Text

While attacking, you may discard a defense token to set 1 die to any face. That die cannot be modified again.

While defending you may spend 1 of your defense tokens to force the attacker to reroll 1 or more dice of your choice.

Maul {

Keywords:assault, cloak, rogue
Card Text

This squadron counts as 'Mandalorian'. For each other friendly 'Mandalorian' squadron at distance 1, you gain adept 1, up to a maximum of adept 2.

Mezine Hinett {

Keywords:counter 1, rogue
Card Text

While a friendly squadron with heavy at distance 1 is attacking a ship with one or more raid tokens, it may add 1 black die to its attack pool. If it does, it must choose and cancel 1 die.

Miktiss {

Keywords:bomber, counter 2
Card Text

After a ship at distance 1 performs a non-counter attack against you, you may attack that ship with a battery armament of 2 blue dice.

Nym {

Keywords:bomber, grit
Card Text

Blue T : If the defender is a ship, you may choose and discard 1 of its defense tokens.

Talonbane Cobra {

Keywords:bomber, grit
Card Text

During your activation, instead of attacking, you may choose 1 friendly non-unique squadron at distance 1 and toggle its activation slider.

The Armorer {

Keywords:assault, cloak, rogue
Card Text

Friendly 'Mandalorian' squadrons at distance 1 with assault gain bomber.

Tyber Zann {

Keywords:dodge 1, grit
Card Text

When activated by a squadron command, you may place 1 proximity mine at distance 1 of you. If you do, you may not move or attack this activation. This mine must be placed beyond distance 1-2 of enemy ships.

Cad Bane }

Keywords:cloak, counter 2, rogue
Card Text

When a squadron at distance 1-2 is destroyed, you may move up to distance 1, even if you are engaged.

Kalani }

Keywords:relay 2, screen
Card Text

At the start of the Squadron Phase, you may move up to distance 3 and toggle your activation slider to the activated side. If you do, the first 4 non-unique squadrons with Ai that you activate at distance 1-2 of this squadron gain Rogue this phase.
